headline: Carnival Unification To Bermuda Parent Reshapes Governance And Investor Options
summary: Carnival Corporation and Carnival plc have agreed to unify into a single Bermuda domiciled parent company. The change will collapse the current dual listing in New York and London into one entity. Headquarters are set to move from Panama to Bermuda once the unification is completed. The company cites simpler corporate governance, a clearer stock market presence, and easier capital markets access as key goals.
